 The Chief Executive Officer of TLK Lifestyle, Temidayo Lucky Kafaru has emerged as one of Nigeria’s most sought-after Sales specialists with a deep understanding of the wine and spirits industry. Those who have worked with Temidayo Kafaru  from his humble beginnings as co-founder of La-scatter sales consults – a company he co-founded with Jolly Jr. Akpojotor and Efosa Omuwa, during their time at the University of Lagos in 2002/2003, described him as extremely intelligent, very skilled – an asset to any organization. Temidayo,  who is currently the Area Manager that covers the New Territories and the Island, Lekki, Ajah, Ikoyi, and Prestige account for Moet Hennessey Africa and Middle East, has continued to be a blessing to Moet Hennessy Africa and the Middle East. He flaunts an intimidating profile – a sales force leader with vast cross-functional experience in Sales and Marketing, spanning over a decade across different wine and spirits markets . An award-winning sales specialist, Temidayo is the youngest Nigerian to be honored by the Universal Peace Federation, (UPF) as an Ambassador for Peace alongside the late Ambassador Olushola, Nigeria’s former ambassador to Ethiopia and former president, Goodluck Jonathan.